            <abstract>
                <p>In some manuscripts of the <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1295Dersan">Dǝrsāna Mikāʾel</ref> the story of the of the Three Youths in the Furnace appears as a commemorative note for Tāḫśāś, in some as a miracle in its own right, also for Ṭǝrr. The story also figures in the <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4035SenkessarDL#Tahs12">Synaxary for 12 Tāḫśāś</ref> (cp. also <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4035SenkessarDL#Tahs2ThreeYouths">Commemoration of  Three Youths on 2 Tāḫśāś</ref>)</p>
            </abstract>
